name: earthdata
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "earthdata" %}
{% set version = "0.3.1" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/earthdata-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 403701e939897f1f5cc0bf020bb2b1e128a1457ec779957a528a91d129bd19be

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --use-deprecated=out-of-tree-build

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.8,<4.0
    - poetry >=0.12
  run:
    - pqdm >=0.1.0,<0.2.0
    - pydantic >=1.5.1,<2.0.0
    - python >=3.8,<4.0
    - python-benedict >=0.25,<0.26
    - python-cmr >=0.4.1,<0.8.0
    - requests >=2.26.0,<3.0.0
    - s3fs >=2021.8.1,<2023.0.0
    - tinynetrc >=1.0, <=2.0

test:
  imports:
    - earthdata
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/earthdata/
  summary: Client library for NASA Earthdata APIs
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jhkennedy
    - betolink
